<div id="review_2183981567" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2183981567" />
    <a title="Malacima" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/71106061-malacima"><img alt="Malacima" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1521893212p2/71106061.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2183981567?book_show_action=true">Nov 20, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Malacima" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Malacima" href="/user/show/71106061-malacima">Malacima</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/71106061-malacima?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/71106061-malacima?shelf=medieval">medieval</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/71106061-malacima?shelf=plantagenet">plantagenet</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2183981567" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5322019125117241043">The book was well written ( as usualy,I have already read the Welsh trilogy and Lionheart (highly recommended)),one that is not filled with the history that are often found in other books of this genre. The story line kept me interested through all 900 and some pages...<br/><br/>Autor writing is full of historical detail. She describes many important battles and politics,revolving mostly around the lives of King Edward IV and King Richard III. The book follows life of Richard of Gloucester from the age of</span>
  <span id="freeText5322019125117241043" style="display:none">The book was well written ( as usualy,I have already read the Welsh trilogy and Lionheart (highly recommended)),one that is not filled with the history that are often found in other books of this genre. The story line kept me interested through all 900 and some pages...<br /><br />Autor writing is full of historical detail. She describes many important battles and politics,revolving mostly around the lives of King Edward IV and King Richard III. The book follows life of Richard of Gloucester from the age of seven,his rise to throne (King Richard III) until his death through treachery at The Battle of Bosworth.<br /><br />The author has clearly done an amazing research into Richard's life and she brings Richard III into life. Book also covers much about Edward the IV, Richard's brother and also other major players (his other brother George Duke of Clarence, his wife and her father Richard Neville-the Kingmaker, Elisabeth (Edward wife) and her Woodville family, Buckingham...etc<br /><br />History has not dealt kindly with Richard for sure.He's accused of the deaths of the “Princes in the Tower”( his nephews) as many other charges. Tudor propaganda did this really well, and Shakespeare contributed to it. But in this book the author convincingly shows other suspects in the murder of the princes and the sequence of events under which this happened.In the future we will definitely find out more about him.<br /><br />All in all the book has many characters, and events and it is difficult to convince all of this in a few sentences. If you are a fan of this genre just read the book. You will not be disappointed.<br /><br />I recently discovered this author and I am amazed. She is realy good in build up of conflict and conclusions, also good in historical research and details and let us not forget her love stories are pretty good.I also love her notes at the end of the book.<br /><br />P.S. I wonder if scientists can make Richard's DNA comparable to the bones found in the Tower</span>
  <a data-text-id="5322019125117241043" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


